Portfolio

Journey Planner

The Journey Planner is a console-based C++ application designed to help users efficiently plan travel routes between different locations. It features the implementation of advanced algorithms like Dijkstra's Algorithm for finding the shortest path and Depth-First Search (DFS) for exploring all possible routes. The project showcases the application of graph theory in modeling the map as an undirected weighted graph and includes an interactive user interface within the console environment. This project highlights my skills in C++ programming, algorithm implementation, and problem-solving in real-world navigation scenarios.

Blood Donation System

The Blood Donation System is a web-based application designed to streamline the process of blood donation by connecting donors with recipients. Developed using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, PHP, and MySQL, the system enables users to register as donors, search for available blood types, and request donations. The project showcases my skills in full-stack development, including front-end design, back-end scripting, and database management, providing a robust and user-friendly platform for blood donation.
